# Nemetic String — Turiya
# Tag: S195 | Encoded: 2026-03-12T00:00:00Z
# Source: 1771907213700_2606957_Exploring+Turiya%3A+Swami+Sarvapriyananda%E2%80%99s+Wisdom.md

Φ(Turiya) = σ(witness|witnessed) ∘ ρ(subject|object) ∘ λ(separation|oneness) ∘ β(self_inquiry|liberation) ∘ δγ(waking|dreaming|deep_sleep) ∘ μ(consciousness|identity) + ε | :non_dual_awareness

## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: witness|witnessed — The foundational distinction: Turiya as the unchanging witness behind all transient states of consciousness.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: subject|object — Maps the experiential relationship between consciousness and its objects before non-dual dissolution.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: separation|oneness — The central Vedantic transformation from apparent separateness to realized unity with Brahman.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: self_inquiry|liberation — Self-inquiry progressively reveals the witness behind all states, growing toward moksha.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: waking|dreaming|deep_sleep — The three ordinary states cycle endlessly while Turiya persists as their invariant ground.
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: consciousness|identity — Structures the relationship between pure awareness and personal identity, showing the true self as unchanging.

## Z-State
:non_dual_awareness — Recognition that witness and witnessed, subject and object, are aspects of one unified consciousness.

## Tendency
σ → 0.85

